3\. Accounting Features

  


Requirements

For the accounting, we need the following features:

  * Sending invoices by email
  * Entering bills, then printing checks for the entire batch
  * Assigning check numbers
  * Printing individual checks (1 check, 2 identical vouchers per page)
  * Reconciling accounts
  * Creating a "Job Quote"
  * Preparing estimates
  * Class tracking and reporting



  


This will include the following standardized reports:

  * Balance Sheet
  * Income Statement (has drill-down into General Ledger)
  * A/R Aging Summary
  * A/P Aging Summary
  * Profit and Loss by Job (with drill-down into General Ledger)



  


We will not need any additional reports on a customer-by-customer basis, or any payroll reports. We will not need any special tools for remitting sales tax or any imports from online banking.

  


This will include a custom Sales Tax report, which will include all invoices for a specific time frame, based on the invoice date. It will prompt for a date range, defaulting to a start date of 1/1 and an indefinite end date. It should only include Open and Paid invoices, not drafts. This report will show the invoice number, customer name, the invoice subtotal, the tax percentage, the tax amount, and the total. It will also show amount totals for all rows.

  


Sales tax payments can be reported using the accounting's General Ledger report.

  


We need the following Pie/Bar graphs:

  * Yardage - bar graph - Monthly and then Yearly -- default view -- total yardage for the company (based on invoice date)
  * Total yardage per customer per year (year or YTD), based on invoice date
  * One pie graph -- one piece is total expense and the other is net profit -- available by month and by year
  * By expenses -- have one pie graph that's just for expenses (by month and by year)
  * Printable in color



  


We will provide a customized estimate based on your template.

  


Discounts for Gra-Rock are provided on a yardage basis.

  * It would be nice to be able to show the discounted amounts, as well as the prepay amount
  * It would be nice to be able to easily apply the discount when paying the invoice.



  


Development Specification

  * For Sales Tax, sends reports to our CPA either monthly or quarterly, and those reports, and he says what they owe, she writes the check and sends it in
  * For Job Quote -- Estimates Matthias Miller 01/03/2019: Small estimate load -- for big jobs, will give a specific estimate -- would be really nice to have forms that say "Job Quote"
